---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getSiteConfig } from '../utils/contentLoader';
const config = getSiteConfig();
---

<BaseLayout title={`Terms of Service | ${config.site.title}`} description="Terms of service for DailyCoder — rules, usage guidelines, and legal information.">
  <div class="container content" style="padding-top: 3rem; padding-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Last updated: March 2026</p>
    
    <div class="article__content">
      <h2>Welcome</h2>
      <p>
        By using {config.site.title} (<a href={config.site.url}>{config.site.url}</a>), you agree to these terms.
        They're straightforward — we want everyone to have a good experience here.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Offer</h2>
      <p>
        {config.site.title} provides coding problems, tutorials, developer tools, and browser-based games
        — all free to use. Our tools run entirely in your browser; we don't process your data on any server.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Use of the Site</h2>
      <p>You're welcome to use {config.site.title} for learning, practice, and personal projects. Please don't:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Scrape or bulk-download content for redistribution</li>
        <li>Attempt to disrupt the site or interfere with other users</li>
        <li>Use the site for anything illegal or harmful</li>
        <li>Misrepresent your identity or affiliation with {config.site.title}</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Content and Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All original content on {config.site.title} — articles, tutorials, tool interfaces, and game implementations —
        is owned by {config.site.title} and its contributors. Problem statements may reference well-known coding problems
        from platforms like LeetCode, HackerRank, and GeeksforGeeks; credit is given where applicable.
      </p>
      <p>
        You're free to use the code solutions and techniques you learn here in your own projects. Just don't copy
        entire articles or pages and republish them as your own.
      </p>

      <h2>User-Generated Content</h2>
      <p>
        If you post discussions, comments, or notes on the site, you retain ownership of your content. By posting,
        you grant us a license to display it on {config.site.title}. We may remove content that's offensive,
        spammy, or violates these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Developer Tools</h2>
      <p>
        Our developer tools (JSON formatter, regex tester, diff checker, etc.) are provided as-is. They process
        everything locally in your browser — nothing is sent to our servers. While we do our best to keep them
        accurate and reliable, we can't guarantee they'll be bug-free. Don't rely on them as your only validation
        step for production code.
      </p>

      <h2>No Warranty</h2>
      <p>
        {config.site.title} is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We work hard to keep content accurate
        and the site running smoothly, but we can't promise it'll always be available or error-free.
        Use the information and tools at your own discretion.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        {config.site.title} and its contributors aren't liable for any damages arising from your use of the site.
        This includes (but isn't limited to) lost data, incorrect solutions, or downtime.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        We link to external sites like LeetCode, GitHub, and MDN for reference. We don't control those sites
        and aren't responsible for their content or practices.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms occasionally. If we make significant changes, we'll update the date at the top
        of this page. Continued use of the site after changes means you accept the updated terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Reach out via our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>
        or email us at <a href="mailto:dailycoder.in@gmail.com">dailycoder.in@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
